transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you for calling Payagra. How can I assist you?

Speaker 2: Yeah, my name is Ray Galaviz, and I have an account with you guys. And I need to cancel it. I need to cancel all my...

Speaker 1: I just received a package from you guys Friday.

Speaker 2: Mm-hmm.

Speaker 1: And so I think that'll do me fine. I'm 64 years old, and...

Speaker 2: Plus, I've developed a rash from your product.

Speaker 1: I don't think it's from our product, but if you have enough supply, what I can go ahead and do for you, Raymond, is that I can go ahead and just pause your prescription.

Speaker 2: We can pause it for half a year.

Speaker 1: And, of course, if you need any supply before that time, you can always call to reorder.

Speaker 2: Yeah. No, I think I just want to cancel it altogether.

Speaker 1: But thank you, though.

Speaker 2: Just to let you know, you are getting rolled by Agra with this, and who have the contract with Pfizer.

Speaker 1: Since we are the only company in the U.S. that sells FDA-approved Viagra

Speaker 2: and who have the contract with Pfizer.

Speaker 1: So if you want to continue to reorder in the future,

Speaker 2: then you might want to pause your prescription for half a year,

Speaker 1: because if you cancel,

Speaker 2: that means that you wouldn't be able to reorder with us in the future at all.

Speaker 1: Yeah, but you guys aren't the only store in town, so neither is Pfizer.

Speaker 2: I'm not worried about that at all.

Speaker 1: Excuse me?

Speaker 2: We are the only ones who sell FDA-approved Viagra.

Speaker 1: Uh-huh. Yeah, I know.

Speaker 2: But still, I want to cancel my order.

Speaker 1: Okay. So you don't want to pause it?

Speaker 2: Nope. No thanks.

Speaker 1: Okay. You're all set.

Speaker 2: Okay. Thank you, ma'am.
